Traditionally, yoga is shared between one teacher and one student. It is only in the recent development of yoga that group classes start popping up. In the age of spirituality meets capitalism, yoga has a face lift. It is now a slimming program, a butt and legs sculpting, a workout and so on. Classes can hold up to 20 people and events/workshops include hundreds. In such event, we are instead focusing on the benefits that you can get from private yoga session.

You might feel that you are not learning what you want, or you might feel out of place in a room of ballerina-like flexible practitioners. However, interestingly enough, nowadays, yoga teaching is coming to a full circle as more and more teachers are offering private yoga classes.

&nbsp;
<h2>Not sure if private yoga classes are for you? Here are some reasons for you to consider one.</h2>
&nbsp;
<h2><strong>4. You get a yoga practice personally tailor to your physique and needs.</strong></h2>
Feeling a little bit unfocused, or feeling you need more drive in your day? Through a private yoga practice, you could convey such feelings to the yoga teacher so as to work towards a sequence that will better prepare you for the events for the rest of the day. When working closely with a yoga teacher, you will also gain insights to how to sequence and tailor your practice according to your mental and physical conditions on that particular day.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>3. You learn the concept of movements.</strong></h2>
A good asana practice should correct structural alignment, build strength, improve flexibility, promote proper functioning of body system and mental steadiness. When you have the attention of a yoga teacher, a detailed explanation of movements and concepts are usually part of the teaching. From this, you will understand the functions (as mention above) of different asanas instead of just chasing their forms.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>2. You grow more in your practice. </strong></h2>
When a teacher is teaching in a group setting, he/she has to make sure that the class teachings are suitable for everyone. It might also be the case that you will not have the chance to clarify doubts on certain teachings of the teacher. You grow, not just in the sense of becoming more flexible or stronger, you are able to grasp the concept of applying your practice into daily living.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>1. You learn concepts and teachings that will help you to cope with the vicissitudes of life</strong>.</h2>
A group teaching is usually focused heavily on asanas practice. The asanas do help to calm the mind, improve concentration and raise awareness, but yoga is more than a physical exercise. Yoga, is a practice for you to discover a clarity of mind through the eight limbs. When you learn the tools of the eight limbs and adopt them to your daily living, you will discover the potential of yoga to positively transform yourself.

